OL,6,FBreakfast Time was an immediate success
OL,7,Fin its early days.
OL,9,FBut once TV-am plunged downmarket and
OL,10,Fsaved itself from disaster, Breakfast
OL,11,FTime started to seem unloved from
OL,12,Fabove.
OL,14,FIt could not compete with its
OL,15,Fdownmarket rival ` nor was it a hard
OL,16,Fnews programme which played to the
OL,17,FBBC's strengths.
OL,3,CReflections on the history of BBC
OL,4,Cbreakfast TV
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34803
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F348A1674627992
OL,6,FYet it was valued, even loved, by its
OL,7,Faudience. Warm and friendly, the
OL,8,Fregular presenters were like extended
OL,9,Ffamily to loyal viewers.
OL,11,FWhen Breakfast Time was relaunched as a
OL,12,Fnews-driven programme in November 1986,
OL,13,Fthe move was controversial.
OL,15,FIt made strategic sense. A clear choice
OL,16,Ffor morning viewers which also gave the
OL,17,Fprogramme a clearer purpose while the
OL,18,Fnew daytime schedule catered for those
OL,19,Fwho wanted the soft features, cookery,
OL,20,Ffashion and chat.
OL,3,CReflections on the history of BBC
OL,4,Cbreakfast TV
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G3/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34804
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F348A1674627992
OL,6,FBut the audience clearly took a while
OL,7,Fto get used to a radically different
OL,8,Fprogramme. The atmosphere was very
OL,9,Fdifferent ` sometimes even sterile `
OL,10,Fand many regular presenters and
OL,11,Fcontributors were dropped.
OL,13,FThis relaunch is sometimes forgotten
OL,14,Fnow as the name remained.
OL,3,CReflections on the history of BBC
OL,4,Cbreakfast TV
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G4/6
